JAPAN: Tokyo rubber futures mostly up on bargain-hunting.Tokyo rubber futures mostly up on bargain-hunting.Tokyo rubber futures ended firmer except for the spot August contract on Tuesday as investors hunted for bargains after all contracts hit life-of-contract lows on Monday, traders said.The spot August contract ended 0.1 yen per kg lower at 129.3 yen. Other contracts ranged from 0.5 yen to 2.0 yen per kg firmer with benchmark January ending up 1.2 at 137.0 yen.The spot August contract failed to rise due to expectations of large deliveries at the spot expiry next week, they said."Sentiment remained bearish as further rises could be capped by selling," one trader said.